snippet.textDisplay: Brother, I would never say he is the best. I have little knowledge of music to be able to decide who is the best. But, I sure have favorites and I appreciate the works of many other Indian talents if they impress me. At times people like Shanker Mahadevan, Vishal Shekhar, Salim Sulaiman, Vishal Bhardwaj and even Amit Trivedi have given us extraordinary songs. But, no one is a master of fusion and they all do it in their own way. And I probably like the Rahman's way of doing it.
